<li><i>Encyclopaedia of the Orient</i>. "<a href="http://lexicorient.com/e.o/ismailis.htm" class="external text" title="http://lexicorient.com/e.o/ismailis.htm" rel="nofollow">Isma'ilism</a>". Retrieved 10 October 2006.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/David_Noel_Freedman" title="David Noel Freedman">Freedman, David Noel</a>, editor. (1998). <a href="/wiki/Anchor_Bible_Series" title="Anchor Bible Series">Anchor Bible Dictionary</a>, article on <i>Antinomianism</i> by Hall, Robert W., <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0385193513" class="internal">ISBN 0385193513</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/J._C._L._Gieseler" title="J. C. L. Gieseler" class="mw-redirect">J. C. L. Gieseler</a>, <i>Ch. Hist.</i> (New York ed. 1868, vol. iv.)</li>
<li>G. Kawerau, in A. Hauck's <i>Realencyklopadie</i> (1896)</li>
<li>Pratt, Douglas. <i>The Challenge of Islam: Encounters in Interfaith Dialogue</i>. Aldershot, Hampshire: Ashgate Publishing Limited, 2005. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0754651223" class="internal">ISBN 0-7546-5122-3</a>.</li>
<li>Riess, in I. Goschler's <i>Dict. Encyclop. de la théol. cath.</i> (1858)</li>
<li>Schimmel, Annemarie. <i>Mystical Dimensions of Islam</i>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0807812714" class="internal">ISBN 0-8078-1271-4</a>.</li>
<li>Weir, Anthony. "Differences Between Bektashism and Islamic Orthodoxy" in <i><a href="http://www.beyond-the-pale.co.uk/albanian4.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.beyond-the-pale.co.uk/albanian4.htm" rel="nofollow">The Bektashi Order of Dervishes</a></i>. Retrieved 10 October 2006.</li>
<li><i>This article incorporates text from the</i> <a href="/wiki/Encyclop%C3%A6dia_Britannica_Eleventh_Edition" title="Encyclopædia Britannica Eleventh Edition">Encyclopædia Britannica<i>, Eleventh Edition</i></a><i>, a publication now in the <a href="/wiki/Public_domain" title="Public domain">public domain</a>.</i></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Peter_Linebaugh" title="Peter Linebaugh">Peter Linebaugh</a> and Marcus Rediker. <i>The Many-Headed Hydra</i>. Beacon Press, Boston, 2000</li>
</ul>
</div>
